{"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "schema", "document", "Document"], "kwargs": {"metadata": {"doc_id": "179caa9c-69e9-42b9-8a39-54b833e22bb6", "source": "NexaCorp Policy Handbook v5.2", "part": "7. Travel, Expenses & Procurement", "section": "7.3 Procurement & Vendor Management", "subsection": "7.3.2 Vendor Qualification & Due Diligence", "raw_content": "Before any new vendor may be engaged, the Procurement team must complete a Vendor Qualification Assessment (VQA) covering: financial stability (Dun & Bradstreet or equivalent); sanctions screening against OFAC, EU, and UN consolidated lists; anti-bribery due diligence proportionate to country risk and contract value; information security assessment for any vendor with access to NexaCorp systems or data; and insurance verification (general liability, E&O/professional indemnity, cyber liability where applicable). WARNING: No NexaCorp employee may begin receiving services from or making payments to a vendor that has not been formally registered and approved in the NexaProcure system. Commitment letters, emails, or verbal agreements with unregistered vendors do not bind NexaCorp legally but may expose the individual employee to personal liability. PART VIII \u2014 DISCIPLINARY & SEPARATION PROCEDURES", "type": "text", "text": "Part: 7. Travel, Expenses & Procurement\n            Section: 7.3 Procurement & Vendor Management\n            Subsection: 7.3.2 Vendor Qualification & Due Diligence\n            Before any new vendor may be engaged, the Procurement team must complete a Vendor Qualification Assessment (VQA) covering: financial stability (Dun & Bradstreet or equivalent); sanctions screening against OFAC, EU, and UN consolidated lists; anti-bribery due diligence proportionate to country risk and contract value; information security assessment for any vendor with access to NexaCorp systems or data; and insurance verification (general liability, E&O/professional indemnity, cyber liability where applicable). WARNING: No NexaCorp employee may begin receiving services from or making payments to a vendor that has not been formally registered and approved in the NexaProcure system. Commitment letters, emails, or verbal agreements with unregistered vendors do not bind NexaCorp legally but may expose the individual employee to personal liability. PART VIII \u2014 DISCIPLINARY & SEPARATION PROCEDURES"}, "page_content": "Part: 7. Travel, Expenses & Procurement\n            Section: 7.3 Procurement & Vendor Management\n            Subsection: 7.3.2 Vendor Qualification & Due Diligence\n            Before any new vendor may be engaged, the Procurement team must complete a Vendor Qualification Assessment (VQA) covering: financial stability (Dun & Bradstreet or equivalent); sanctions screening against OFAC, EU, and UN consolidated lists; anti-bribery due diligence proportionate to country risk and contract value; information security assessment for any vendor with access to NexaCorp systems or data; and insurance verification (general liability, E&O/professional indemnity, cyber liability where applicable). WARNING: No NexaCorp employee may begin receiving services from or making payments to a vendor that has not been formally registered and approved in the NexaProcure system. Commitment letters, emails, or verbal agreements with unregistered vendors do not bind NexaCorp legally but may expose the individual employee to personal liability. PART VIII \u2014 DISCIPLINARY & SEPARATION PROCEDURES", "type": "Document"}}